Judgment in an application by Media24 to livestream Henri van Breda's murder trial will be handed down shortly before the case starts in the Cape Town High Court today. Jump to bottom Judge Siraj Desai will decide at 10:00 whether he will allow a livestream of the trial.Henri Van Breda is charged with three counts of murder, one of attempted murder, and one of obstructing the course of justice.Van Breda was arrested 17 months after his parents, Martin, 54, and Teresa, 55, and his brother Rudi, 22, were killed in their home on the luxury De Zalze golf estate in Stellenbosch in the early hours of Tuesday, January 27, 2015.His sister Marli, 16, survived.Henri van Breda is set to go on trial in the Western Cape High Court today, two years after his parents and brother were killed with an axe.&nbsp;Early morning commentary from passer-by calling for justice for #VanBreda family. Man shouts that Henri "hacked his bloody family to death". pic.twitter.com/Sjmh2Ul0lI#VanBreda Defense Pieter Botha and Lorinda van Niekerk have arrived at the WC High Court. pic.twitter.com/92fSQcqrfDTriple murder trial of Henri #VanBreda starts today at WC High Court. Camera crews set up; media from as far as Australia at proceedings. pic.twitter.com/BMttF0MdyR Jump to top